The paper discusses the application of deep learning techniques to biomedical question answering, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also employs transfer learning techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL) research, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper involves information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques, which are relevant to cs.IR and cs.AI, respectively. Finally, the paper uses neural networks, which are a type of computational model commonly used in the field of neural engineering (NE), making cs.NE a possible sub-category as well.
